{
  "text": "I will make a statement that I have extracted from the physics of Dewey Larson, which may or may not be close to what we are trying to explain. Larson says that all is motion, which we can take as vibration. And that vibration, which is pure vibration, and is not physical in any way or in any form or in any density, by vibration. By the first product of that vibration, is what we call the photon or the particle of light. I was trying to make an analogy between this physical solution and the concept of love and light. Is this close to the concept of love creating light or not? I am Ra. You are correct.",
